President Barack Obama has sent a letter to the Speaker of the House, stating that the national emergency with respect to the Democratic Republic of the Congo will continue beyond October 27, 2010. The situation in the country, characterized by widespread violence and atrocities, poses a significant threat to regional stability and the foreign policy of the United States. Therefore, the President has determined that it is necessary to maintain the national emergency and the measures blocking the property of certain individuals involved in the conflict.